            <statement>
              <p>
                <m>\displaystyle \int (3x^2-2x)\sqrt[3]{x^3-x^2}\dx{x}</m>

              </p>
            </statement>
          </exercise>  
          <exercise> 


            <statement>
              <p>
                <m>\displaystyle \int \sin^5(\theta)\cos (\theta ) \dx{\theta }</m>
              </p>
            </statement>
          </exercise>
          <exercise>


            <statement>
              <p>
                <m>\displaystyle \int \sec(7x)\tan(7x)\dx{x}</m>
              </p>
            </statement>
          </exercise>
          <exercise>


            <statement>
              <p>
                <m>\displaystyle \int \frac{1}{(1+x)^2}\dx{x}</m>
              </p>
            </statement>
          </exercise>
          <exercise>


            <statement>
              <p>
                <m>\displaystyle \int \sin( \theta )\sec^2(\cos(\theta )  \dx{\theta }</m>
              </p>
            </statement>
          </exercise>
          <exercise>


            <statement>
              <p>
                <m>\displaystyle \int \frac{\inverse\sin (\phi) }{\sqrt{1-\phi
                }}\dx{\phi }</m>
              </p>
            </statement>
          </exercise>
          <exercise>


            <statement>
              <p>
                <m>\displaystyle \int x\sqrt{1-x}\dx{x}</m>
              </p>
            </statement>
            <hint>
              <p>
                There are really only two choices for the substitution, and
                it is not clear that either will work. It is normal, and
                very human, to sit and stare at the problem wondering what
                to do when this happens. Don<rsq/>t do that. It is normal,
                but it is also unhelpful. Make a substitution, work out the
                new integral and hope that it is one you can do. If not,
                start again and make the other substitution.
              </p>
              <p>
                But don<rsq/>t wait for the problem to solve itself. It
                won<rsq/>t.
              </p>

            </hint>

          </exercise>


          <exercise>


            <statement>
              <p>
                <m>\displaystyle \int e^{2x}\sqrt{1-e^x}\dx{x}</m>
              </p>
            </statement>

          </exercise>
